        "text": "I checked that exact page with Firecrawl, and the SEO is **not fully correct**. The content itself is strong, but the page-level technical/meta setup has some real issues.\n\n**Main findings**\n\n- **Bad `<title>` tag**\n  - The actual page title being exposed looks like: **“In Article Audio Player”**\n  - That is a serious SEO problem.\n  - The article headline is **“A New Front in the Boycott Wars”**, and that should be the title base.\n\n- **Conflicting robots directives**\n  - Firecrawl surfaced:\n    - `index, follow, max-image-preview:large...`\n    - and also **`noindex`**\n  - That contradiction is a big red flag. If `noindex` is present anywhere in the final rendered output, Google may drop the page from search.\n\n- **Meta description exists, but it needs cleanup**\n  - Current description:\n    - “Gabe Stutman investigates the BDS protests against restaurants they perceive to be linked to Israel, which has forced some to close., In Article Audio Player”\n  - The trailing **“In Article Audio Player”** is junk and should not be there.\n\n- **Canonical tag appears missing**\n  - I did not find a canonical for this URL in the scraped page output.\n  - For article pages, you want a self-referencing canonical:\n    - `https://momentmag.com/the-new-front-in-the-boycott-wars/`\n\n- **No visible JSON-LD structured data found**\n  - I did not see Article schema in the page output.\n  - That is a missed opportunity for article SEO and richer search understanding.\n\n- **Content structure is mostly fine**\n  - One clear **H1** is present.\n  - The article has strong body copy, internal topical relevance, image usage, category/tag context, and date/author signals.\n  - So the **content SEO is decent**, but the **technical/meta SEO is weak**.\n\n**What I’d fix on this page specifically**\n\n1. **Fix the title tag immediately**\n   - Recommended:\n   - **A New Front in the Boycott Wars | Moment Magazine**\n   - If they want stronger keyword targeting:\n   - **A New Front in the Boycott Wars: BDS Protests Target Restaurants Linked to Israel | Moment Magazine**\n\n2. **Remove the bad audio-player contamination**\n   - “In Article Audio Player” should not appear in:\n     - title\n     - meta description\n     - OG tags\n     - Twitter tags\n\n3. **Fix robots so it is unambiguous**\n   - Use only:\n   - `index, follow, max-image-preview:large, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1`\n   - Remove any accidental `noindex`.\n\n4. **Add a canonical tag**\n   - Point it to:\n   - `https://momentmag.com/the-new-front-in-the-boycott-wars/`\n\n5. **Rewrite the meta description**\n   - Suggested version:\n   - **Gabe Stutman investigates how BDS-linked protests are targeting restaurants perceived to be tied to Israel, forcing some businesses to shut down.**\n   - Keep it clean, human, and around normal snippet length.\n\n6. **Add Article schema**\n   - Include:\n     - headline\n     - author\n     - datePublished\n     - dateModified\n     - image\n     - publisher\n     - mainEntityOfPage\n   - This is especially important for magazine/article content.\n\n7. **Make sure OG/Twitter tags are complete and clean**\n   - `og:title`\n   - `og:description`\n   - `og:url`\n   - `og:type=article`\n   - `og:image`\n   - `twitter:card=summary_large_image`\n   - `twitter:title`\n   - `twitter:description`\n\n**Bottom line**\n\n- **Content quality:** good\n- **On-page structure:** mostly good\n- **Technical SEO for this page:** **needs fixing**\n- **Biggest issue:** the page appears to be leaking audio-player text into SEO fields, and the robots directives may be conflicting\n\nIf you want, I can turn this into a **developer-ready SEO fix checklist** for that exact page/template.",
